caption: The bar has a fantastic holiday theme, that really sets the mood. The holiday drinks, as well as the normal drinks, are both creative and delicious.  The food is very tasty and really adds the island charm to the experience.
Friendly staff, old school Tiki drinks made in the true Tiki way. The food was awesome and tasty. Highly recommend for any Tiki followers.

Amazing gem in the heart of U street.  The speciality cocktail options are concentrated in rum concoctions and are second to none in the city.  The best way to go is to order several dishes and share (depending on hunger and amount of ppl).  Absolutely order the Crab Dip and the Beef Nachos.

Went there today. They open at 5pm. I arrived at 4:57pm. I asked if I could seat on the patio while I waited for my friend (I'm 9 months pregnant). The waiter refused... I left and will never be coming again.  Following up on your response to my comment: your waiter was extremely rude and not helpful. He did not direct me to your front door, he told me I would have to wait until the official opening and then enter through the front door, only after I asked why I was being refused entrance. At 9 months pregnant, I take covid mitigating measures extremely seriously so your answer is not only out of line, it also shows how little respect you have for your customers. You can be sure I'll advise all of my friends to never set foot in your bar. Not the kind of publicity you'd hope to have in these difficult times, bur I'm afraid you brought it on yourselves...
Food was terrible! I’d recommend going to the bar next door for food and drinks.
Underdog tiki spot. Staff is VERY knowledgeable and love tiki. If you love tiki I 100% recommend this spot!
The food and drinks tonight were awesome! Stephen was a fantastic server; extremely attentive and made us feel so welcome. We're definitely looking forward to our next visit.
Different vibes combined with delicious food and amazing service!

Archipelago was outstanding! Since I moved to DC, I've been wondering where I could find great cocktails after going to a number of places with sugary, weak, tasteless drinks. We loved the cocktails here. They were on point in terms of portions, recipe, and presentation. Our server was super nice and chill. They have a ton of excellent vegan options. The food was flavorful, well executed, and a great value. I will definitely be back again and again.
Great Happy Hour spot. Food is on point and the drinks range in strength but never falter in being delicious.
don't eat here just drink here
Great drinks and vibe. Really liked the low music volume so people could have a conversation, even at the bar!

This place was not very crowded for a Saturday night, which is what I prefer. However, there were only two bartenders for an entire restaurant and bar area so service was incredibly slow. The bartenders were so behind they kept losing track of who was next and people were cutting the line. When this was pointed out the bartender snapped back because she was very overworked. Management really needs to consider another bartender on busy nights
Nice vibe with low lighting and good servers. Name of the drinks are fancy with shape of the glasses even fancier but taste as good.

Cute place with tropical and island style cocktails. Friendly and attentive staff. Hard to determine where the establishment is located since there is no signage and windows are covered in woven grass curtains.
Cocktails are great, the communal ones especially, and it is fun to try out their huge selection of rums. Great food, especially if you love hot and numbing peppercorns!

Probably one of my favorite spots in DC. Been here a few times and have really enjoyed it. It's a full on Tiki bar selling Tiki drinks with a range of Chinese inspired dishes. I really enjoy the Dan Dan Noodles and the Opaque Voodoo, it's even served in a shark head which is pretty unique. Definitely worth the trip, and I'm sure I'll return many more times again.
Reserve the 1.5 floor section for quiet conversation.
Great food and amazing kitsch rum drinks! And they come in amazing tiki cups. Good happy hour deals and the food comes in huge servings.
Best tiki bar in DC.
The drinks are so good, and the food is delish.

I loved the place from the moment I walked through the veiled entrance. They make the tiki bar experience a transition into another world where you can relax and change your mindset. We're talking downtown DC, which is one of the most stiff and buzzkill environments on earth. And yet, they make going to a bar here fun The drinks are great, and the bartender was totally pro. The music is the right mix of off the wall surf and 60s garage. The place is clean, and well ventilated. The bathrooms are clean and nice. I would recommend just hanging out here all night and forgetting about the rest of the town.
Authentic tiki, amazing drinks, great decor and atmosphere. Delicious food was the perfect accompaniment to a great retreat from a cold DC night.
Great atmosphere and the staff is super knowledgeable
Great drinks, small plates, and atmosphere. Wonderful staff!

(Translated by Google) I really like December decoration since I love Hawaii, their cocktails are a bit different for those who don't like conventional good vibes good service!  (Original) Me gusta mucho sí decoración de diciembre puesto que me encanta Hawái, sus cócteles son un poco diferentes para los que no les gusta lo convencional buenas vibras buena atención!

I was at the bar on first floor last night. I politely asked the female bartender at the bar booth for water twice. She yelled at me and others to move over and served others the drinks. I didn’t get water while I was there. The feedback at the place, the bartenders should be polite and respectful to the consumers, and they should serve people the drinks no matter what.

What a gem! This is one of the places we knew we had to try when we were in DC. We love tiki bars, and this one was on the list. We went in December for Sippin' Santa, and it was everything we expected! The drinks were incredible and the food was great as well! We will come back again!
Visited for sippin santa popup. The atmosphere and drinks were incredible and service was excellent.
My Pina colada was too sugary and the Ti punch was unpleasant. I enjoyed the steamed bun and the ambiance.

We can't get enough of this place! Amazing drinks, food, and most of all: the folks who work their craft here! Take a ride share to get here, walk, or metro - tiki drinks are as strong as they are tasty! Not a rum fan? They have a full bar, and several non-rum tiki options. My favorite food to get is the smashed cucumber and the mapo tofu - and my friends rave about the "mountain" of szechuan pork (or maybe it's beef?) nachos you can get! Want to try a more intimate setting and get your gourmet tiki on? Make a Lost Island reservation on a Friday or Saturday night and feel like you're at an exotic locale - sometimes you need the escapism ;)  Come hungry, bring friends or make some at the bar - you're in for a treat!
Great Atmosphere!
I've lived here for 15 years and never knew this place existed. Great staff and great, fun drinks

The drinks are deceptively stiff, but extremely tasty. Dangerous! Definitely a place I will go back to with friends coming into town. Did not have any food, but it looked phenomenal (and that was before I had anything to drink).
Pretty cool place. Only had their nachos but they were great and the atmosphere was nice. Would go back for their food for sure.
Nice tiki bar to hang out located  in the center of the u Street area
Great happy hour prices. Good service.
Great selection of cocktails and food was good!
Cozy pleasant place with quite some fancy drinks.
Bunch of tasty tiki drinks! Want to do even more of the menu and will definitely come back
They have nice drinks, and a good happy hour.
Mai Tai good.  Not sweet.  Classic tiki menu.  Excellent.
Great tiki bar with delicious drinks and nice decor!

This place was so much fun...the food was delicious and beautifully presented (we got the dan dan noodles, potatoes, egg rolls, and chicken buns), and that goes double for the drinks! Service was great. The decor was delightful. Definitely try this place out!
Great drinks. Great service. Great atmosphere. I am really glad we came here. I would like to try everything on the menu. The nachos are great for a small group.
There is a secret menu... fun hki

Real tiki drinks, not overly sweet junk you find at some so called tiki bars.  Their house drinks are all solid and they have a separate classics menu by request.  The food is also a standout, I don’t even bother with dinner anywhere else all their stuff is so good I fill up there.  The Dan Dan Noodles, tiny fish, hot chicken steam buns and the nachos are all standouts.
Identity Crisis.... this place is a no for me. Weird vibes, mediocre food, expensive drinks, and pretty horrible service. Bruh do not come here and save your money.

I used to like this place but after a series of unpleasant experiences I have decided I will not go back. About a year ago I had my first negative experience with archipelago. As I was sitting at a booth drinking with friends a very large cockroach crawled onto my arm. I felt a tickle and when I looked and realized what it was I flung it onto the floor. The waitress/bartender proceeded to run out and attempt to smash it with her shoe. Additionally, there was lipstick on my water glass. No apologies were given for either of those things. After that experience I started to avoid the place but some of my friends still liked the place so I  would only go if they insisted. The last experience I had was with the "speakeasy" (if you can even call it that). We had to wait until a spot opened up and then a waiter walked us up to the very unimpressive room. The drinks were decent and we ordered and received a large plate of nachos. A 6th person in our party showed up and that's when the problem occured. The person squeezed into our booth easy enough and suddenly a waiter came over and told us that they only allowed up to 5 people. We thought this was odd but we understand there are rules so we asked if we could just finish our large plate of nachos and go back to the downstairs bar. The waiter stared blankly at us and said no with no apology (reoccurring experience here). Without offering to help us carry our large plate of nachos we walk of shamed down to the now full downstairs area. We then huddled in a group and took turns holding and eating the large plate of nachos. It's sufficient to say I will not be going back.
Nachos and a couple zombies

Happy hr 5-7 has amazing tiki drink selections as well as a tasty selection of asian-pacific island good options. My go tos are the Ti punch and noodles. The ambience is pretty chill and great for date nights. The staff are knowledgeable about the drinks and YES , they don't skimp on the booze. The drinks are Tres boozy. Highly recommend!
Great Tiki bar in the middle of the city. Some classic tikis mixed with unique choices. Worth a visit to take a tiki staycation.
Their pina colada is delicious
(Translated by Google) Demo  (Original) Awesemo
The banana dolphin!!
Great value overall, especially during happy hour.
Cute decor
Fun tiki bar
Always a fun atmosphere and fun crowd. Drinks are very creative and have a tropical flare. Bar tenders are friendly and provide great and quick service.
The atmosphere is welcoming, the bartenders are personable, and the drinks are fire. Super stoked I checked out this place. I will always recommend from my hometown tiki bar. Thank you all!!
An excellent tiki bar with many traditional options and some more unique ones. The secrets in the Pineapple of Hospitality are worthy of the intrigue.

Really great food and service! The presentation is so cute everything comes in miniature Chinese food cartons that are also very chic! My friend and I were having such a great conversation we didn't notice one menu item missing when we got our food! (A server got bumped and dropped it) but they quickly brought us a replacement and complimentary shots in the cutest tiki shot glasses with a small elephant sitting on top! Great atmosphere and great food I highly suggest 💕
Good drinks, terrible service. Can't remember the last time I took effort to write a bad review, but I couldn't let anyone else waste their time here without knowing how bad it's gotten.
They made a banana into a dolphin!
Best pizza in the city.
Amazing
Excellent ambiance, service, and rum selection. Every drink was carefully crafted and true to "tiki" style. Will definitely be going again!
Fun drinks
Strong, tasty drinks
Nice and chill spot on busy U st. Drinks are excellent but on the pricier side due to the amount of time it takes to make them.
We found this place by accident after dinner and it was surprisingly a really good tiki bar! The vibe and the service was really nice and the drinks were quite tasty.
Colorful Tiki Bar with Amazing Drinks !! 🍹

Very lovely service and the food was absolutely delicious! Not very much gluten-free options though, and as good as the drinks were, they were overpriced. Pleasant, creative atmosphere, almost like a beach restaurant/bar in the city.
Drinks were good but wouldn't go back .. not good food
Fun tiki bar with old classics and some more inventive variations.
Amazing drinks and hardworking bartenders
You'll walk right past it lol awesome drinks! They set mines on fire 🥳
Awesome drinks and service!
Drinks amazing food ok
Best cocktails ever
A little expensive, but a great experience from a U St bar.

This place was a huge surprise...the drinks are great and so was the crowd. The servers were nice enough to suggest variety of rum drinks to try out. Will definitely go back again. Also, the music was really good.
Tiki done really well!
Great drinks, fun atmosphere

Great atmosphere! The drinks were good, the room selection was awesome! Took friends that do not drink there as well, they were very pleased with their virgin Pina Coladas. We did not get a chance to try the food but it looked and smelled good. Bartenders were very friendly and helpful as well.

Archipelago really leans into the tiki bar vibe but not in a way that's too over the top. It has a decent happy hour, with a couple signature cocktails+ beer/wine, and the food deals are really cheap (think $3 for two large egg rolls, $6 for noodles, etc). I had the piña colada and while it was a bit too sweet it totally did the trick for a happy hour at the start of spring. All of the food we had was good - fine - but I won't be going back for the food. The patio is small but well situated for people watching if that's your thing! If you're looking for a different kind of spot on U Street to hang out, this is a great option.
The tiki atmosphere is so cute! Delicious and strong drinks & yummy asian-inspired food.

This place is awesome and kind of hidden but in plain sight if that makes sense. We went to grab some drinks and ended up eating. Everything we tried was fantastic. The drinks were creative and the service was great.
Try the Zombie... It's delicious and packs a punch!
Great drinks and bar food. Great service and very knowledgeable bartenders.

Excellent beverages with a great tiki vibe. I have built tiki bars professionally and their approach lends itself to a modern vibe with a touch of classic bamboo and ceramic mugs. Interesting Mai Tai and If The Phone Doesn't Ring, Its Me is a fantastic bridge to exotica for Bourbon drinkers.
Great tiki drinks, excellent service, nice atmosphere. Top notch tiki bar.
Incredible tiki experience. Highly recommended!
Fun spot with quirky drinks. Get the spiced potatoes. You're welcome. ;)

If you love trying all different kinds of fun drinks, go here. It's now a new mission to try the entire menu, but each one I've had so far has been delicious! (And without feeling like you're getting skimped on alcohol)

Favorite bar in DC. Dick Dale is always pumping through the speakers and these guys have an elaborate menu of classic and original cocktails and more rum you can shake a stick at. Please come here and drink cocktails.

The drinks here are innovative and not too cloying. I love the atmosphere, the staff is lovely, and it’s never too loud to have a decent conversation. The menu is simple but delicious, and the patio is a wonderful area for a date.
Great cocktails!
This is the best bar in dc
Food was good. The sheets in front of the door make it a little hard to know if that's the way you're supposed to go in.
Fun drinks and decor!
Tropical decor that changes with the season. Fun drinks. Limited food options. Awesome staff.

I enjoy coming to this place on occasion. I love the ambience and surfer/guitar music selection. The reason I don’t come more frequently is that, despite the cocktails being very good, it’s pricey at $12-14 each. The drinks are unique and they have subtle flavors, which is a plus.  I’ve most recently tried the Dan Dan noodles and hot chicken steam buns and thought they were pretty good though more spicy than expected/hoped. I think the food tends to be spicy hot in general, or at least for my taste.  If in doubt, I’d recommend checking out a happy hour here during the week to see if you like it.
Good stuff, not great. But the prices and atmosphere are right. Check it out.
Decent food, great drinks, tiki spirit.

(Translated by Google) Very good bar I really liked the cocktails and the food. Take advantage of happy hour to try several meals, pasta is special.  (Original) Muy buen bar. Me gustó mucho los cócteles y la comida. Aprovecha el happy hour para probar varias comidas, es especial la pasta.

We came in at 9:30 on Saturday night.  It was a bit crowded but we found two seats and were brought a menu.  The menu and website said food served until 11 but we were told the kitchen had closed.  I think when the waiter saw our expression he tried to see if there was something that they would still make us so he came back and said that they would make us Dan Dan noodles and their late night fried rice. It was pretty disappointing to have only two choices of what to eat we ordered two drinks and the food it came out pretty promptly but service was a bit off...sat with empty glasses for a while and they never refilled our water.  It was not what I expected as a friend of mine who is in the business (mixologist/bar manager) had recommended it.  Not sure if I would go again.
Drinks were good

Anyone who sees my other reviews knows - I know tiki. Archipelago gets bonus points for being the only TRUE tiki bar between Baltimore and DC. However, even without those bonus points it does a damn good job. Many tiki bars get the drinks right but the food is quite lacking. Archipelago has the drinks and the food and the decor (in that order). Their custom mug is only so so, but at least they have one!

It's TIKI TIME! Prior to Archipelago, the last time I had a tiki drink was in NYC about four years ago. I had heard good things about Archipelago, and we wanted to celebrate with some tiki cocktails.  Over the holidays, they busted out the Sippin' Santa's Surf Shack pop-up. The decorations were very holiday appropriate. Colored lights, holiday lanterns, garlands, and tiki totems with Santa hats.  I started with a Kris Kringle Colada. while my fiancé got a Grinch Grog. Both drinks were great. Afterwards, we shared a Pineapple of Hospitality. If you like tiki drinks, this is definitely the place to go. We also ordered some wontons in red oil and dan dan noodles, and both dishes were good too (even better than some actual restaurants in the district).  Overall, we had a really fun time at Archipelago. I know we'll be back for more tiki drinks!
Incredible!  Amazing drinks.  Lively atmosphere.

I went to the Christmas edition of this tiki bar (Sippin' Santa) and i wasn't dissapponted. It wasn't too crowded or empty, I was able to immediately find seats for 2 and put my name down for a table of 4 and the wait wasn't unbearable. Service was great at all the levels and the drinks were delicious! I wish I had paid more attention to the mug choice as well as the drink choice. I'll definitely come back to try out the regular tiki bar.
The best Tiki bar in DC!
Came for special Christmas cocktail program - some fun unusual combinations. Food more than just snacks and enough to absorb some of that over proof rum.
Fantastic drinks although on the pricier side.
Awesome tiki drinks and Asian/Pacific inspired food.

I love this place. It's perfect for a winter escape. The tiki drinks are amazing and the food is on point (Chinese but with some Western additions: try the Dan Dan noodles, ham and cheese sliders, and nachos!)
A unique place for being in the city

A modern tiki bar with a great cocktail lineup. Popped in for the Christmas tiki spin off and had a great time. Jordan and Caleb did a great job holding down the bar and didn't steer us wrong. Sadly, Jordan is just stage-ing, but the service was spot on and friendly. Try the dan dan noodles, bit salty but go great with the cocktails. Eggplant was also good, and can't go wrong with a coconut heavy rum drink. Highly recommended!
The drinks were pretty but overpriced. Service was ok.
What a find! Fabulous drinks - delicious and unique food - friendly and efficient staff. We loved Archipelago. (What's not to like about a flaming pineapple?)
The tiki drinks are outrageous... love the cups and the way they present the drinks. The sliders are amazing too.
Great cocktails!

Its a tiki bar!! Cocktails are average 13$ but you are paying for the atmoaphere for sure. Awesome place to kick back and chill, sadly no couch though. Seems like there should be a couch for some raisin
This place is amazing.

Great atmosphere!! Low key, tiki style. Drinks were delicious. Food was excellent. The crab rangoon dip melts in your mouth! I wish the fried chips it came with were a bit less greasy, the dip is so good it could be served with anything!!
It was good!
Awesome and awesome and awesome
Crazy good noodles

Went to this bar on Friday and none of the bartenders acknowledged me or my friend. After being ignored (waited 10-15 minutes) we sat down and then one of the the bartenders (with a shaven head) proceeded to harass us and tell us that if we did not purchase a drink we would need to leave. I find it hilarious he took an issue with us not buying a drink when we sat down, but ignored us when we attempted to get service at the bar. I truly believe we were discriminated against. If you are black, I would not come to this bar. Never have I been asked to leave a bar because I have yet to purchase a drink. Sad this type of activity occurs in 2018. I would avoid this establishment at all costs. No one deserves that type of harrassment and treatment.

Sit at the bar and watch the action as the OCD bartenders make these fantastic drinks. We watched person after person come in and order canned beer for $8.   Please don't do that. You are missing the point.  These fantastically delicious cocktails where in the $12 to $15 range. There's a special menu that you can ask for that has old school drinks on it too. I recommend the Fog Cutter and the Macadamia chi chi.
Interesting modern tiki bar  on U street. Great tasting food
Try the crab Rangoon dip and tip your server. I had a great drink that had "anarchy " in the name. Drink it.
Best tiki bar in town. Good snacks and amazing cocktails. Friendly staff.  Bonus: flaming tiki drinks!
My husband competed in a Tiki Drink Competition and Pig Roast and it was really cool. Cool people, nice comfortable Tiki decor and overall good vibes
Drinks are pricey but very fun. The atmosphere is lovely. It's a great stop on any night of bar hopping on U St.

I love this place. The food is excellent, the drinks are even better. If you are looking for more of an authentic tiki bar experience, this place is definitely the place to be. The bar tenders are also very well versed in their craft. Archipelago is definitely on the list of places to frequent.
Great, authentic tiki drinks & a cool atmosphere
Great atmosphere and service
Awesome tiki bar with great classic drinks and quality Chinese food.
Great tiki vibe, on a quiet night it's one of my favorite spots in DC.

One of the many interesting places I've found in the area..  The bar has quite a few tasty specialty drinks.  I only sipped my friends though, because all of the drinks have brown alcohol in them, and I simply don't drink it 🤷🏽‍♂️.  The food is tasty, cheap, and quick.  I'll be back
Expensive, a bit hipster, but totally cool
Awesome time bar in DC! Great time!
Home for The Malolo Boyz after hours hang out feels like home :)
Great tiki bar! If you love tiki, this is the place to go.

Loved this place! The decor is amazing and the drinks are awesome. It's always nice feeling like youre on a tropical island after being in the city for so long. The Mai Tai and Pina Colada were amazing and came in the cutest tiki mugs! The food looks great, but didnt have any and the rooftop was closed for a private event. Definitely would go back.
Great rum based cocktails
Nice little bar with tropical island style. But it got very crowd and very loud inside.
The drinks are fun, the food is okay
The ham and cheese sliders are SO good, you must try them

This place is great! More food on the menu than they have on their website, and there's lots of great options (I've attached a pic of the full menu). The drinks are also very delicious. We had a great time here and would recommend!
Fantastic drinks, great food and great service. A must while in the area.

(Translated by Google) I really love this TIKI BAR. As a lover of tikis bars, I was pleasantly pleased with the decoration of the place, thought out to the smallest detail, the music, the Hawaiian movies in Black and White that are shot on the second floor, the patio with lights with a beautiful view of the U Street. The cocktails are delicious, with spectacular TIKI MUGS and delicious taste. Large collection of rums and the bartenders know what they are doing. The typical food of TIKIS restaurants. Correct but nothing too elaborate. Without a doubt, a place that takes you out of the ordinary and makes you have a spectacular time in DC.  (Original) Me súper encanto este TIKI BAR. Como amante de los bares tikis quede gratamente complacida con la decoración del lugar, pensada hasta el más mínimo detalle, la música, las películas hawaianas en Blanco y negro que se ruedan en el segundo piso, el patio con luces con una vista re linda del U Street. Los cócteles son riquísimos, con TIKI MUGS espectaculares y el sabor delicioso. Amplia colección de rones y los bartenders saben lo que hacen. La comida propia de los restaurantes TIKIS. Correcta pero nada muy elaborado. Sin duda un lugar que te saca de lo común y te hace pasar un momento espectacular en DC.
Great atmosphere!!! Very Tiki
Fun tiki bar with light Chinese snacks.

This place had good food and drinks, but the drinks seem a bit overpriced. $12-16 cocktails are ok, but not when the servings are very small and minimally decorated for a tiki place. The fried rice serving was very small too, coming in a 2x2x2 inch Chinese takeout box.
The best place for rum inspired drinks  and appetizers in DC
Went for drinks and appetizers. Both very good.
The worst customer service on u st ,
I have never had a bad time here. The drinks are strong and wonderful. Service is excellent. 100% recommend. The most expensive drink is worth trying. Just order food too...
Delicious mixed drinks, relaxed atmosphere

We came here during the day on a Saturday that the Funk Padade was coming through. We were able to hang out, get incredible cocktails, and watch and listen to the parade. The service from Caleb on the patio was great, and I was pleased as punch throughout this afternoon. That may have been in part to the delicious and strong cocktails! Each one has a unique cup, garnishing, and is themed, and they are delicious. One warning, consuming a lot of them ends up being fairly sugary (natural sugars, not added sweeteners) and will get you way past tipsy. Great experience, I'll be back!
The Hospitality Pineapple!!! 😊 Awesome!!!!  The Dan-dan Noodles and the Crab Rangoon Dip are to die for!!!

This place has a great location on U street. I love sitting outside. Their outdoor patio is great. The drink prices are great. The customer service is always on point. This is definitely a place you can go and just kick back and enjoy yourself. The only recommendation I would suggest is more options not food on the menu.
The food was a bit salty

At first, this tiki bar looks a little run of the mill, with the usual decor and a standard menu with some goofy house specialty cocktails, but one look at their garnish skills and a peek at the fantastic rum collection behind the bar belies a serious streak. After you're done fooling with the regular menu, ask the bartender to see the other cocktail list, delineated by decade. This place is legit.
Drinks were super strong. One off the best kept secrets on U Street.
Fantastic food and strong tropical drinks. Cool servers. Neat interior.
Cool drinks with lots of straws and decorations

I love anything Tiki and this place was sure to draw my attention and keep it. I'm so glad I decided to come here even though I received unbelievable mixed reviews from coworkers. They were wrong. Great happy hour prices, amazing piña colada, and get the ham and cheddar sliders, they are amazing. Get here early for a spot on the almost always crowded deck. LOVE IT.
Fun drinks, with a dope rum list.

Great tiki bar but service was slow.  I had been wanting to try this tiki bar for a while and took the opportunity to do so while catching up with a high school friend.  My visit was late on a Sunday night so I am giving them the benefit of the doubt on the service.  Place is pretty uncluttered and well lit, I imagine on a busy weekend night that is a plus.  They had a diverse menu of tiki drinks and the food menu looked appetizing (all finger foods,) but I didn't try the food.  I had three different tiki drinks and each one was very good and the bartender was great about recommending which to try based on my taste. The one downside was that it was hard to get a drink order, even though the place was not busy, probably 12 customers total.  I am giving them the benefit of the doubt that this was due to it being late on a Sunday night, so I plan to go back soon for more drinks and to try the finger foods.

This bar is okay. If you are looking for a tiki bar atmosphere on U St (I don't know who is, but someone might be) its your only option. The whole drink menu is filled with super sweet fruity cocktails. I'm not a fan, but I'm sure someone is. The have decent happy hour deals, and the food is not so bad. The best thing this bar has to offer is it's unique atmosphere. But I've never been particularly excited about coming here.
Amazing happy hour deal solid food great drinks good staff. Especially nice in the winter gives a mental feeling of being in the tropics.

This place was awesome. Came here for a quick bite before going out. Service was great, place feels good - very friendly and fun. Drinks were delicious as well as cute. We ended up going back later in the night cause it was such a fun place.
4 words: happy hour flaming pineapple. You're welcome.
The stream buns are amazing and spicy! The black beam chicken is tender and juicy. I only had one drink which was the Puka Puka Punch and it was tasty and not too sweet.

Very well done tiki bar with a great mix of classic tiki and new tiki cocktails and great food that can be enjoyed alone or paired with the above . Friendly, enthusiastic and knowledgeable staff are the icing on the cake !

Full disclosure, I was already half wasted when I tried Archipelago for the first time the other night. This place gets five stars from me for one reason, the Mai Tai is crazy delicious, and made made with Smith and Cross Navy Strength rum and some delicious citrus shrub instead of Curacao. For all I know, everything else there could be garbage, and even if it was (which I suspect not) I would go back for that drink. Cheers!
Good tiki drinks
Awesome drinks and service. Love the theme of the drinks. Drinks are on the pricey side but they are tasty and flashy.

Love Archipelago!  Tiki bars are so fun!  The decor is great.  Pineapple of Hospitality and the Banana Daquiri are great.  The food is decent.  I wouldn't go here specifically for dinner but it's nice for a bite with drinks
Fun and beautiful cocktails, with plenty of alcohol
Great tiki bar
Tiki bar with a casual neighborhood vibe.
A cozy little bar. I felt the drinks should be stronger for their price point. Cocktails seem to contain mostly ice and minimal alcohol.

Came here as part of 2017 Tiki Trail. The decor was great. You truly felt like you were in a tiki bar or room. The cocktails were also good. The bartenders were attentive as were the waitstaff. I enjoyed my time here.
Some (not all) of the bartenders and servers are extremely rude and act as if you are really disrupting their awful lives by asking for a drink during Friday evening bar rush.
Favorite Happy Hour in the city. Excellently made drinks and food that will blow your socks off.

As far as Tiki themed bars go, they can be pretty campy and frankly not very fun. Archipelago, however, is great! With plenty of open space, as well as a cozy bar area, this place is pretty awesome if you're looking to surround yourself in some island goodness for a bit. The drinks are as authentic as the decor, and you'll be happy you stopped in.
(Translated by Google) Good vibes. Cooky decor  (Original) Good vibes. Cooky decor
I've never been there but it seems pretty okay. 4/5 stars.
Loved it and great staff will find you a drink that is amazing.
The food is Asian but the bar it Tiki ? The need a better menue
Went for dinner last night and it was great. We ordered the eggs, chicken steam buns, Dan's noodle, and the wings and the flavors on everything were good. Definitely would go here again.
Drinks are on the somewhat expensive side, but you get what you pay for in decor, ambience, and, of course, strength of the beverage. May I recommend the Captain Cody?
Fun tiki bar and good food. Often crowded, but a cool place to hang out anyway
Solid choice
Fun place with huge, strong themed drinks. There's also an upstairs but it's never been open when I've gone and you can't smoke on the patio.

This is a really fun place for happy hour especially as the weather is heating up.  I had the Ti Punch which was very boozy but good if you like rum with some light mixers for flavor.  My friends got the pineapple of hospitality.  Which was interesting.  I would suggest it as a one time thing and only at the happy hour prices.  The atmosphere is very cool, the staff was friendly and the glassware is all unique and cool.
Cool spot with strong drinks
Tried a few appetizers and drinks here. Service is consistent yet not hovering. The drink options were fun and served with considerable creativity. I had the pina colada - How fun!

We didn't try the food, because we had just eaten somewhere else, but the drinks and the atmosphere were very nice. Staff was friendly and shared checking up on all tables so no-one was left waiting and no staff member was overwhelmed.

Rum, Rhum, Ron, and Cachaca. If you love the spirit, or want to you have to go here. Great tiki mugs and topically inspired cocktails! Also other liquor options but why not get that sugar cane juice in your belly?

Super awesome ambience. Has an upstairs and patio. Patio space can get crowded...fast. Happy hour is from 5-7pm with the awesome Pineapple of Hospitality being the flaming star. Parking is limited to street and timed.
Get the pina colada.  Just do it.
A great place to relax and forget you are in the city. Try Pina Colada.
A tiki rum bar in the heart of the city offering a great selection of creative, boozy cocktails.
Nice drinks
Gradually increasing the kitsch, which is a good think. Great rum and coke, which is suprisingly challenging in DC
Great tiki cocktails and pretty good bites
Crab Rangoon dip is a must. The wings are good.  Don't get fruity drunk.
Fun place where you almost feel like you are on a tropical vacation. Great happy hour deals. Our group ordered the large serving of nachos and enjoyed them. Service was a bit slow at times.
We love this place. Great drinks, great food, fun atmosphere, and the service is always pleasant (and attentive, even when it's packed.)
The service was pretty slow, we had to seat ourselves, and get our own menus but that is because there was only one waitress.  The appetizers are pretty good but we didn't try one of the tiki drinks.
Great (cheap) happy hour, super fun tiki cocktails, delicious food, and great service!
Great tiki drinks in the tacky coconut glasses. Happy hour from 5-7.
We had Captain Cody for our drinks. OMG, sooooo good. Love the atmosphere, Great service.
DC's tiki bar! Great original cocktails as well as classics. Friendly staff and a shrine to Magnum P.I.!
Very cool place
Very cool place with inventive tiki cocktails.

At first glance, this place looks expensive for what you're getting. It's not cheap, but you find out why once you get your drinks: expertly mixed, full of unique and strong flavors, and STRONG! You only need one, maybe too.  The food is decent too, but who goes to the tiki bar for food?
Tasty drinks with a small but creative food menu combined with a fun atmosphere brings back memories of Hogo.
Great food, great drinks, great tiki! You really can't go wrong here.
Get there before 7 for great happy hour prices. The Pina Colada is made with fresh pineapple and then sent through the frozen machine for incredible smoothness. Ask about Tom Selleck.....
There's nothing like it in the city!  The ambiance feels like you're on vacation, the drinks are incredible (and beautiful), and the food is delicious.  Recommend the ham and cheese sliders.
